                "caption": "Figure 4:Tasks and Real-to-Sim Policy Evaluation correlations.(Left) We apply SimFoundry to a DROID setup using a single Franka arm (top two rows), and a bimanual setup with two YAM arms (bottom row). Our tasks span multiple types of manipulation, including multi-step, articulated object interaction, and bimanual coordination (Clear Tablenot shown, more details in AppendixI). (Right) SimFoundry outperforms the state-of-the-art baseline PolaRiS[32]in simulation-based evaluation correlations. Each marker shape represents a different task from the left. Additional details in AppendixGandFigure G.1.",
